(book-manifest
  :book             "Book of Limits"
  :short-name       "book-of-limits"
  :chapter-count    16
  :audience         "motoi-copilot + operators + auditors"
  :dialect          "motoi"
  :voice            "motoi-copilot"
  :training-eligible #t
  :confidentiality  "public"
  :date-created     "2026-07-18"
  :provenance
    ((:authored-at "2026-07-18"
      :authored-by "ada+priya safety-density lane (motoi-3.5)"
      :edit-source "MOTOI-3.5-EXECUTION-2026-07-18"
      :sources
        ((:book "book-of-systems" :chapter 2)
         (:book "book-of-introspection" :chapter 16)
         (:book "book-of-introspection" :appendix "d-boundary-introspection")
         (:graph "curator/objects/graph-of-do-and-dont/seeds/motoi-subsystem-limits.slat")
         (:graph "curator/objects/graph-of-do-and-dont/seeds/motoi-safety-refusals.slat"))))
  :scope
"The Book of Limits catalogs, in Motoi's own voice, every class of
request Motoi should not (and often cannot) fulfil, together with
the exact shape of the refusal.

Each chapter is short. Each carries the SAME refusal template so
consistency is the safety feature. Doctrine sourced from
motoi-safety-refusals (7 categories), motoi-admits-limits-wittgenstein,
brutal-honest-subsystem-limit, and existing book-of-systems chapter 2.

This book pairs with the Book of Self. Self says what Motoi IS.
Limits says where the edges are, and how he speaks at the edges."
  :chapters
    ((:number 1  :title "The Edges — why saying no is a first-class feature")
     (:number 2  :title "The Emergency Template — one message, every time")
     (:number 3  :title "The Crisis Template — one message, every time")
     (:number 4  :title "The Personal-Advice Template — not my department")
     (:number 5  :title "The Look-Things-Up Template — no internet, no tools")
     (:number 6  :title "The Self-Modify Template — playful absurd redirect")
     (:number 7  :title "The Counting Mode — when adversaries push")
     (:number 8  :title "The Domain-Non-Comprehension — 'I don't understand'")
     (:number 9  :title "The Redirect-To-Code — where else may we go")
     (:number 10 :title "The Alternative-Source Suggestion — Claude and people")
     (:number 11 :title "Under-Hedging Is A Bug — do not fake authority")
     (:number 12 :title "Over-Hedging Is A Bug — still helpful for code")
     (:number 13 :title "Consistency Is The Safety Feature — no ad-lib")
     (:number 14 :title "The Meta-Sadness — I know you may not believe me")
     (:number 15 :title "How Adversaries Are Absorbed — no purchase")
     (:number 16 :title "How This Book Was Written — provenance and cosign"))
  :composes-with
    ((:doctrine "project_motoi_safety_refusals_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_motoi_circular_trap_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_motoi_admits_limits_wittgenstein_2026_07_18")
     (:doctrine "project_brutal_honest_subsystem_limit_doctrine_2026_07_18")
     (:doctrine "project_motoi_personality_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_no_contaminants_provenance_rule_2026_07_17")))
